  "response": "Definition-based questions that require only one-word answers are typically designed to elicit simple, precise responses. Here are some examples:\n\n1. **What is the opposite of \"hot\"?** (Cold)  \n2. **What is the capital of France?** (Paris)  \n3. **What is the chemical symbol for water?** (H2O)  \n4. **What is the largest planet in the solar system?** (Jupiter)  \n5. **What is the study of living organisms called?** (Biology)  \n6. **What is the process by which plants make food?** (Photosynthesis)  \n7. **What is the color of pure snow?** (White)  \n8. **What is the shape of Earth?** (Sphere)  \n9. **What is the smallest prime number?** (Two)  \n10. **What is the name of Earth's natural satellite?** (Moon)  \n\nThese questions are designed to test knowledge of specific facts or concepts and require concise, one-word answers.",
